(*
  Go+ grammar, v0.5.1 — a delta over spec/grammar-v0.5.0.ebnf. Every
  production not listed here is unchanged.

  REMOVED: GoplusNameDirective (`//goplus:name`, from v0.1.0/v0.2.0). Lowered
  names never needed a directive — the names are contained in the code:

  - A generic method (R).M lowers to a package function named M itself,
    cased so the result is exported iff BOTH R and M are exported. When
    the name is shared inside the package — another type's method, an
    enum method, or any package-scope declaration — every collider falls
    back to the receiver-prefixed concat(R, M) form. A collision that
    survives prefixing is a hard error naming both origins; the fix is
    renaming a method, never annotating one.
  - Enum variant structs keep their existing scheme (the variant's own
    name, enum-prefixed when shared across enums), now with no override.

  This file and the Godog feature suite under features/ are together the
  authoritative specification of Go+.
*)
